Janet Mary Tupper1

F, #597644, b. 28 February 1929, d. April 2015

Last Edited=24 Mar 2019

Janet Mary Tupper was born on 28 February 1929.1 She was the daughter of Sir James Macdonald Tupper, 4th Bt. and Agnes Jean Collins.2 She married William John Couldwell, son of William Blythe Couldwell, on 17 March 1951.1 She died in April 2015 at age 86.3

She was educated in 1951 at Vancouver General Hospital School of Nursing, Vancouver, British Columbia, Canada.1 From 17 March 1951, her married name became Couldwell. She lived in 2003 at 50-5880 Hampton Place, Vancouver, British Columbia, Canada.1

Children of Janet Mary Tupper and William John Couldwell

Susan Janice Couldwell+2 b. 18 Feb 1953

Sandra Lee Couldwell+2 b. 15 Sep 1954

Dr. William Tupper Couldwell+2 b. 15 Dec 1955

William John Couldwell1

M, #597646, d. April 2012

Last Edited=24 Mar 2019

William John Couldwell was the son of William Blythe Couldwell.2 He married Janet Mary Tupper, daughter of Sir James Macdonald Tupper, 4th Bt. and Agnes Jean Collins, on 17 March 1951.1 He died in April 2012.3

He gained the rank of Wing Commander in the Royal Canadian Air Force Reserve.1 He graduated with a Doctor of Medicine (M.D.)1 He graduated with a Maste of Surgery (C.M.)1

Dr. William Tupper Couldwell1

M, #597647, b. 15 December 1955

Last Edited=24 Mar 2019

Dr. William Tupper Couldwell was born on 15 December 1955.1 He is the son of William John Couldwell and Janet Mary Tupper.2 He married Marie Francoise Simard.1

He graduated with a Bachelor of Science (B.Sc.)1 He graduated with a MDCM.1 He graduated with a Doctor of Philosophy (Ph.D.)1 He lived in 2003 at 643 North Perry's Hollow Road, Salt Lake City, Utah, U.S.A.1
